{
  "answer": "The work *Kalpabuddha* dedicates each of its first five chapters to one of the five Tathāgatas (collectively the Pañcatathāgata), assigning them specific internal organs as their bodily abode (with chapter 6 providing a summarizing account of their manifestation as the five senses). Chapter 1 covers Vairocana (heart), chapter 2 covers Akṣobhya (lungs), chapter 3 covers Ratnasambhava (spleen), chapter 4 covers Amitābha (liver), and chapter 5 covers Amoghasiddhi (gall bladder). Each chapter ends with the specified formula.[^1][^2][^3][^4][^5]\n\nHere are verbatim quotations of the residence-formulas from the first, second, and fifth chapters (the others follow the identical pattern):\n\n> Now, as for his residence in the body, **the inside of the heart is his abode**.[^1]\n\n> Now, as for his residence in the body, **the inside of the lungs is his abode**.[^2]\n\n> Now, as for his residence in the body, **the inside of the gall bladder is his abode**.[^5]\n\n[^1]: *Kalpabuddha*, [Chapter 1, p-e1c8df](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/01/translation/#p-e1c8df).\n\n[^2]: *Kalpabuddha*, [Chapter 2, p-5a580a](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/02/translation/#p-5a580a).\n\n[^3]: *Kalpabuddha*, [Chapter 3, p-68d96e](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/03/translation/#p-68d96e).\n\n[^4]: *Kalpabuddha*, [Chapter 4, p-60c6c3](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/04/translation/#p-60c6c3).\n\n[^5]: *Kalpabuddha*, [Chapter 5, p-8f8def](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/05/translation/#p-8f8def).",
